comment: Not a good day at work, but it had it's highlights I guess. Most equipment wasn't working, and we were running the machinery at very slow pace. Then one of the managers comes over and happily asks me how's it going. I was like, "fucking terrible, man".
He snickered and said that normally people tell him "fine" even if it's raining fire, and that he appreciated my honesty. tl;dr unintentionally got brownie points at work.
got a big mug of tea and delicious dinner in my stomach. It's going pretty good so far.
